desc: The TEK gene encodes a receptor tyrosine kinase (RTK) protein also known as angiopoietin-1 receptor. Signaling via the TEK receptor has roles in angiogenesis, cell migration and proliferation (PMID: 12816861, 9204896, 14665640, 18425120, 19223473). The role of TEK in cancer depends on the predominant ligand binding the receptor, with angiopoietin-1 having an agonist effect and promoting angiogenesis and angiopoietin-2 having an antagonistic role (PMID: 20651738). TEK mutations are rare events in human cancers (cBioPortal, MSKCC, Dec. 2016).
